race.comment: MAGENTA SHORES (8) needed the first-up outing and then missed narrowly at Goulburn over this distance. She's capable of using the inside barrier and has more to give. Penza is reunited, and she's ready to win. SPICY SURPRISE (7) was much better at Hawkesbury at her second race start and will go close with that under the saddle. Draws awkwardly but will hit the line hard. TOUSSAINT (14) resumed and worked home well to grab third at long odds at Kembla Grange over 1200m. Will drift back but wind up late, and is sure to keep improving. SATIN'S LEGACY (13) and CRATHIE KIRK (9) are both third-up and heading in the right direction. Neither can be ruled out.
